      <body>
         <div type="edition">
            <ab>
               <lb n="1"/>
                  <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"/>
               <lb n="2"/>
                  ni<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"/>
               <lb n="3"/>
                  <persName>
                     <name type="praenomen" key="Gnaeus"><expan><abbr>Gn</abbr><ex>aeus</ex></expan></name>
                     <name type="gentilicium" key="Trebonius">T<supplied reason="lost">rebonius</supplied></name>
                  </persName> 
               <lb n="4"/>
                  et
                  <persName>
                     <name type="gentilicium" key="Trebonia">T<del rend="erasure">e</del>rebo<supplied reason="lost">nia</supplied></name>
                  </persName>   
               <lb n="5"/>
                  parent<supplied reason="lost">es fecerunt sibi et</supplied>
               <lb n="6"/>
                  liberti<supplied reason="lost">s libertabusque</supplied>
               <lb n="7"/>
                  post<supplied reason="lost">erisque</supplied>
               <lb n="8"/>
                  eoru<supplied reason="lost">m</supplied>.
            </ab>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>
               The parents Gnaeus Trebonius and Trebonia made (this) for him, and their freedmen
               and freedwomen and their descendents.
            </p>
         </div>
         <div type="apparatus">
            <p>
               Line 4: Spelling error: carver originally inscribed Terbo[...], but the "e" was scratched out and a smaller "e" was inserted
               between the "r" and "o" to yield "Trebonia."
            </p>
            <p>
               Line 5: Olcott supplies "filio suo b.m. et," but the CIL addition of "fecerunt sibi et" seems more appropriate.
            </p>
         </div>
